.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH g-branch 1  "g-branch " 
.SH NAME
g\-branch \- Enhanced branch listing, `git branch` passthrough, or `branch squash`
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBg\-branch\fR [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fIREST\fR] [\fIsubcommands\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Enhanced branch listing, `git branch` passthrough, or `branch squash`
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
[\fIREST\fR]
When no `squash` subcommand: forwarded to enhanced list or `git branch`
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
g\-branch\-squash(1)
Collapse all commits on the current branch into one (from merge\-base with base)
.TP
g\-branch\-help(1)
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
